The paper deals with learning from a mix of fully-labeled supervised data and contextual bandit data, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the theoretical and empirical aspects of the problem, which are relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer engineering (cs.CE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
